text:
The first grader showed me the book he drew. I laughed at the cute pictures. 

First Grader: “What are you laughing at?”

Me: “The pictures.”

Him: *Glares*

Me: “They’re cute.”

Him: “Aliens invading the earth is funny? Really?"

text: Only 0.9% of women’s college basketball players will go pro. Even those who do go pro don’t make huge dollars. One can imagine a lot of local businesses that would gladly pay a women’s college sports star for an endorsement. But the NCAA forbids it.
author: DrewHampshire

text:
Only 1.2 percent of men’s college basketball players will go pro, per the NCAA.

Many more could convert their brief fame into a great post-college nest egg by cutting their own endorsement deals.

The NCAA forbids this b/c it would cut into NCAA & college endorsement revenue.
author: DrewHampshire

text:
There are an awful lot of TV ads featuring college mascots.

Why?

Advertisers who want to be associated with college basketball have to cut ads with mascots or coaches because the NCAA forbids them from paying the people they’d prefer to feature — the athletes.
author: DrewHampshire
